1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:02,970
♪

2
00:00:14,147 --> 00:00:17,751
Dio: Enyaba, there’s something
i’d like to ask you.

3
00:00:17,784 --> 00:00:20,153
What does it mean to live?

4
00:00:20,187 --> 00:00:23,223
Enyaba: It’s to obtain
all that one desires.

5
00:00:23,257 --> 00:00:26,227
If you were to distill life
into its essence,

6
00:00:26,260 --> 00:00:28,162
that is what it would be.

7
00:00:28,195 --> 00:00:30,097
A lust for riches,

8
00:00:30,130 --> 00:00:33,433
a desire for fame,
food, love, and lovers,

9
00:00:33,467 --> 00:00:34,768
that is life’s goal.

10
00:00:34,801 --> 00:00:36,369
( Chuckles )

11
00:00:36,403 --> 00:00:40,073
Dio: But one must always fight
to get what one wants.

12
00:00:40,107 --> 00:00:42,643
Isn’t that correct, enyaba?

13
00:00:42,676 --> 00:00:45,579
Enyaba: Indeed. ( Chuckles )

14
00:00:45,612 --> 00:00:47,781
Dio: And if the battle is lost

15
00:00:47,814 --> 00:00:50,750
and one fails to obtain
what one desires most,

16
00:00:50,784 --> 00:00:54,421
the result is frustration,
pain, and a sense of failure.

17
00:00:54,454 --> 00:00:57,090
One carries the wound
into the future,

18
00:00:57,124 --> 00:00:58,826
into the next fearful battle.

19
00:00:58,859 --> 00:01:02,363
I believe conquering that fear
once and for all

20
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,365
is what it means to live.

21
00:01:04,398 --> 00:01:07,101
The one who stands
at the pinnacle

22
00:01:07,134 --> 00:01:09,770
is the one who has no fear.

23
00:01:09,803 --> 00:01:12,572
Do you understand, enyaba?

24
00:01:12,606 --> 00:01:14,775
Enyaba: I was
the one who told you

25
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:16,543
about the existence
of your stand

26
00:01:16,577 --> 00:01:18,012
and how to use it.

27
00:01:18,045 --> 00:01:20,414
Also you have an immortal body.

28
00:01:20,447 --> 00:01:23,250
Is there anything
you could possibly fear?

29
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:24,818
Dio: Perhaps, old woman.

30
00:01:24,852 --> 00:01:27,822
Enyaba: Hmm.
What burdens you, my lord?

31
00:01:27,855 --> 00:01:30,458
Dio: The joestar bloodline.

32
00:01:30,490 --> 00:01:33,827
Enyaba: Hmm? Joestar?
They worry you?

33
00:01:33,861 --> 00:01:36,163
Those worms are mere trash.

34
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:38,598
Your enemies
are no match for your stand.

35
00:01:38,632 --> 00:01:41,101
Dio: Yes, but I must
believe it’s destiny

36
00:01:41,134 --> 00:01:42,602
when the lives of those worms

37
00:01:42,636 --> 00:01:44,171
are so thoroughly entangled
with mine.

38
00:01:44,204 --> 00:01:47,140
It is a fate that has
been written for us all

39
00:01:47,174 --> 00:01:48,609
from the very beginning.

40
00:01:48,642 --> 00:01:50,377
Let me be clear.

41
00:01:50,410 --> 00:01:53,246
It is not the joestars
that I fear,

42
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:57,184
but the fact that I can never
underestimate their bloodline.

43
00:01:57,217 --> 00:01:59,119
In order to obliterate all fear,

44
00:01:59,152 --> 00:02:01,755
I have decided
that I must remove the joestars

45
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,356
from the cogs of fate.

46
00:02:03,390 --> 00:02:06,693
Enyaba: You want to go
and eliminate them yourself,

47
00:02:06,727 --> 00:02:10,431
simply because you feel that
they cannot be underestimated?

48
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:11,465
Dio: Yes.

49
00:02:11,498 --> 00:02:12,799
Enyaba: Foolishness!

50
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:15,369
You should never engage
in such trivial matters!

51
00:02:15,402 --> 00:02:17,337
They are beneath
someone of your stature!

52
00:02:17,371 --> 00:02:19,640
I have sent seven stand users
to command--

53
00:02:19,673 --> 00:02:21,675
the empress,
the wheel of fortune,

54
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:23,310
the hanged man and temperance,

55
00:02:23,343 --> 00:02:24,845
the emperor, and the devil--

56
00:02:24,878 --> 00:02:26,646
all of them on the move

57
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,382
and ready to strike
whenever you call.

58
00:02:28,415 --> 00:02:30,284
Thanks to these allies,

59
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:33,720
you need not take
any action yourself, lord dio.

60
00:02:33,754 --> 00:02:36,390
( Cackling )

61
00:02:38,659 --> 00:02:40,494
( Joseph gasps )

62
00:02:45,899 --> 00:02:47,901
♪

63
00:02:55,242 --> 00:02:57,244
( Singing in Japanese )

64
00:03:30,811 --> 00:03:33,647
( Men gasping )

65
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,814
Sailor: A freighter.

66
00:03:34,848 --> 00:03:36,817
Sailor #2:
I didn’t see it at all.

67
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:38,585
( Jotaro groans )

68
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:40,821
Joseph: Jotaro, something’s
bothering you, isn’t it?

69
00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:42,522
Are you worried there might be

70
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:44,224
another stand user
on this freighter?

71
00:03:44,258 --> 00:03:46,360
It’s not ideal,
but we could handle it.

72
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:48,896
Jotaro: Not quite.
Strange they lowered the stairs,

73
00:03:48,929 --> 00:03:52,699
but there’s not a single soul
to be seen around here anywhere.

74
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:53,701
Joseph: Eh?

75
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:55,736
♪

76
00:04:00,274 --> 00:04:02,710
Polnareff: This ship came
all this way to rescue us.

77
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:05,212
There has to be
some sort of crew onboard.

78
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:08,782
Even if they’re all stand users,
i’m getting on this boat.

79
00:04:08,815 --> 00:04:10,517
I’m done drifting in circles.

80
00:04:10,551 --> 00:04:11,752
( Men grunt )

81
00:04:14,288 --> 00:04:15,856
Joseph: Hmm?

82
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:19,326
Jotaro: Take my hand, kid.

83
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:20,727
I’ll help you get up.

84
00:04:20,761 --> 00:04:23,530
Girl: Um...

85
00:04:27,334 --> 00:04:28,435
Blehh!

86
00:04:30,337 --> 00:04:32,372
Jotaro: Good grief.

87
00:04:32,406 --> 00:04:34,408
( Ship creaking )

88
00:04:35,409 --> 00:04:37,411
♪

89
00:04:43,417 --> 00:04:45,419
( No audible dialogue )

90
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:50,958
( Creaking continues )

91
00:04:54,895 --> 00:04:56,964
Joseph: Hey,
what’s with this ship?

92
00:04:56,997 --> 00:04:59,266
There’s no captain
in the control room,

93
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:01,301
there’s no engineer
in the radio room.

94
00:05:01,335 --> 00:05:02,503
There’s no one anywhere.

95
00:05:02,536 --> 00:05:04,271
And yet, look at this.

96
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,639
All the gauges and machinery

97
00:05:05,672 --> 00:05:07,407
are working properly,
just like normal.

98
00:05:07,441 --> 00:05:09,643
Polnareff: Maybe they’re
just all in the bathroom

99
00:05:09,676 --> 00:05:11,611
with a bad case of the runs.

100
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:13,280
Joseph: Hey!
Isn’t anyone around?!

101
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:15,382
Girl: You have to see this.
Come here! Quick!

102
00:05:15,415 --> 00:05:16,416
- Polnareff: Hmm?
- Joseph: Eh?

103
00:05:18,919 --> 00:05:22,689
Girl: An ape.
There’s an ape inside that cage.

104
00:05:24,725 --> 00:05:26,627
( Orangutan grunts )

105
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:28,462
Kakyoin: It’s an orangutan.

106
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:30,831
Joseph: Who the hell cares
about a friggin’ ape?!

107
00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:32,366
Let’s split up

108
00:05:32,399 --> 00:05:34,434
and find whoever’s
been feeding this thing.

109
00:05:34,468 --> 00:05:36,403
♪

110
00:05:36,436 --> 00:05:37,437
( Girl gasps )

111
00:05:39,673 --> 00:05:42,776
( Orangutan sighs )

112
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:45,613
( Girl gasps )

113
00:05:51,418 --> 00:05:52,386
Avdol: Well?

114
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:53,620
Sailor #3: Hmm.

115
00:05:53,654 --> 00:05:56,590
It doesn’t appear
to be broken, but...

116
00:05:57,624 --> 00:05:58,592
Joseph: Uh...

117
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:00,393
Eh?

118
00:06:03,564 --> 00:06:04,698
Avdol!

119
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:07,000
That sailor! Watch out!

120
00:06:07,034 --> 00:06:08,602
( All yell )

121
00:06:10,003 --> 00:06:11,571
( Girl screams )

122
00:06:11,605 --> 00:06:12,840
Jotaro: Oh, good grief.

123
00:06:12,873 --> 00:06:14,508
That isn’t any way

124
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:17,044
to greet a lady you’ve
never met before, now, is it?

125
00:06:17,077 --> 00:06:18,845
( Sailors gasping )

126
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:21,882
Sailor #3: But no one
was touching the controls.

127
00:06:21,915 --> 00:06:23,784
Sailor #2:
I saw that crane move,

128
00:06:23,817 --> 00:06:25,919
even though there was
no one operating it.

129
00:06:25,953 --> 00:06:28,422
I don’t believe in ghosts,
but what the hell?

130
00:06:28,455 --> 00:06:29,957
Sailor #3: I saw it, too.

131
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:32,659
That crane impaled him
all on its own.

132
00:06:32,693 --> 00:06:35,896
Joseph: Keep your guard up.
There’s someone hostile here.

133
00:06:35,929 --> 00:06:38,732
Hey, don’t touch the machinery.
You got that?

134
00:06:38,765 --> 00:06:40,767
If it moves
or runs on electricity,

135
00:06:40,801 --> 00:06:42,536
don’t lay a finger on it.

136
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:44,004
If you want to live,

137
00:06:44,037 --> 00:06:46,473
then you’ll do exactly
as I tell you. Understand?

138
00:06:46,507 --> 00:06:47,775
Get into the cabin below,

139
00:06:47,808 --> 00:06:50,044
and stay there
until I tell you otherwise.

140
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:52,079
( Sailors murmuring )

141
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:56,583
Joseph: Did any one of you see

142
00:06:56,617 --> 00:06:58,486
even a glimpse of a stand
just now?

143
00:06:58,519 --> 00:07:00,021
- Polnareff: I didn’t.
- Avdol: My apologies.

144
00:07:00,053 --> 00:07:03,056
I was the closest to the crane,
and yet I felt nothing.

145
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:05,025
I should have been able
to sense something.

146
00:07:05,058 --> 00:07:06,793
Kakyoin: All right.

147
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:09,430
I’ll send hierophant green
to take a look around the ship.

148
00:07:11,932 --> 00:07:13,934
♪

149
00:07:16,904 --> 00:07:19,607
Girl: I have no idea
what’s going on,

150
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:22,877
but scary things keep happening
whenever you guys are around.

151
00:07:22,910 --> 00:07:24,512
Could you guys be jinxed?

152
00:07:24,545 --> 00:07:25,780
I’ve heard about people

153
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:27,781
who cause disasters
that endanger everyone.

154
00:07:27,814 --> 00:07:30,784
If that’s what you are,
i’d better stay away.

155
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:31,818
( Gasps )

156
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:41,395
Joseph: I have
just one bit of truth for you,

157
00:07:41,428 --> 00:07:42,663
so listen closely.

158
00:07:42,696 --> 00:07:45,499
Whatever happens,
we’re on your side.

159
00:07:45,532 --> 00:07:48,068
Girl: Uh...Huh.

160
00:07:48,101 --> 00:07:49,502
Joseph: Stay safe.

161
00:07:49,536 --> 00:07:52,105
Make sure you stay
with the others. Got it?

162
00:07:52,139 --> 00:07:53,707
Girl: Mm-hmm.

163
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:55,742
♪

164
00:08:13,427 --> 00:08:14,728
( Orangutan grunts )

165
00:08:14,761 --> 00:08:16,763
( Grunting )

166
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:20,734
( Sighs )

167
00:08:24,471 --> 00:08:27,474
( Grunts )

168
00:08:27,508 --> 00:08:29,844
Girl: Do you want me
to open the cage for you?

169
00:08:29,877 --> 00:08:32,980
But I can’t.
I have no idea where the key is,

170
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:35,115
and you’re too big to let out.

171
00:08:36,517 --> 00:08:39,487
You’re giving me an apple?

172
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,489
But it doesn’t make any sense.

173
00:08:41,522 --> 00:08:43,090
This apple’s
been cut with a knife,

174
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:44,891
and the color
hasn’t really changed yet.

175
00:08:44,925 --> 00:08:46,960
It looks totally fresh,

176
00:08:46,994 --> 00:08:48,896
like it was cut a second ago,

177
00:08:48,929 --> 00:08:51,565
so I guess there really must be

178
00:08:51,598 --> 00:08:53,467
someone hiding
somewhere on this boat.

179
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,868
Where is the person
who feeds you?

180
00:08:54,902 --> 00:08:56,871
Has he gone off
and left you here?

181
00:08:56,904 --> 00:08:57,905
- ( Wood flicks )
- Huh?

182
00:08:59,673 --> 00:09:00,908
Orangutan: Mmm.

183
00:09:02,209 --> 00:09:04,178
Girl: Whoa.
You’re a pretty smart monkey.

184
00:09:04,211 --> 00:09:06,013
Who trained you to do that?

185
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,682
( Orangutan blows )

186
00:09:09,683 --> 00:09:11,185
( Grunting )

187
00:09:15,822 --> 00:09:18,491
( Girl gasps ) No way.

188
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,894
A monkey like you is
actually into looking at...

189
00:09:20,928 --> 00:09:23,664
( Swallows ) Pinups of girls?

190
00:09:23,697 --> 00:09:25,766
( Orangutan sighing )

191
00:09:30,170 --> 00:09:32,072
Sailor #3: Hey, kid,
be careful there.

192
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:33,073
( Girl gasps )

193
00:09:33,106 --> 00:09:34,808
Sailor #2: They say an orangutan

194
00:09:34,842 --> 00:09:37,011
has five times the strength
of a normal human,

195
00:09:37,044 --> 00:09:39,113
so it could
easily rip off your arm.

196
00:09:39,146 --> 00:09:42,750
Sailor #3: Come on. Stay with us
in the room on the other side.

197
00:09:42,783 --> 00:09:44,652
Don’t go off by yourself.

198
00:09:44,685 --> 00:09:46,153
Girl: Oh, okay.

199
00:09:46,186 --> 00:09:48,188
( Orangutan grunting )

200
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:53,760
♪

201
00:09:58,665 --> 00:10:00,200
Kakyoin: It’s inconceivable.

202
00:10:00,234 --> 00:10:03,104
I’ve had hierophant green
search every inch of this ship,

203
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:06,239
but I can’t find a single sign
of human life aboard.

204
00:10:06,273 --> 00:10:07,975
We’ve searched
every pipe and crevice,

205
00:10:08,008 --> 00:10:09,710
but still came up empty-handed.

206
00:10:09,743 --> 00:10:10,777
( Jotaro sighs )

207
00:10:10,811 --> 00:10:12,313
Sailor #3: Anything?

208
00:10:12,346 --> 00:10:14,715
Sailor #4: It’s no use.
I can’t get a connection.

209
00:10:14,748 --> 00:10:17,251
Sailor #3:
Well, try again, damn it.

210
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:19,319
( Girl sniffing )

211
00:10:20,754 --> 00:10:22,322
Ehh, gross.

212
00:10:22,356 --> 00:10:24,792
I feel sticky
from the salt water.

213
00:10:24,825 --> 00:10:26,293
( Groans )

214
00:10:26,326 --> 00:10:28,328
Huh? Hmm.

215
00:10:28,362 --> 00:10:29,363
( Handle creaks )

216
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:34,268
( Gasps )

217
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:36,703
( Humming a tune )

218
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:45,012
( Screen clatters )

219
00:10:46,079 --> 00:10:48,014
( Continues humming )

220
00:10:48,048 --> 00:10:49,049
( Giggles )

221
00:10:56,056 --> 00:10:58,058
♪

222
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:06,700
( Sighs )

223
00:11:11,839 --> 00:11:13,741
Huh? ( Gasps )

224
00:11:13,774 --> 00:11:14,842
( Orangutan grunts )

225
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:16,877
( Girl whimpering )

226
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:21,582
♪

227
00:11:33,493 --> 00:11:35,495
( Orangutan grunting )

228
00:11:44,438 --> 00:11:46,807
( Girl gasping )

229
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:48,809
( Orangutan sighing )

230
00:11:55,782 --> 00:11:57,217
( Girl whimpering )

231
00:11:57,251 --> 00:11:58,219
( Orangutan grunts )

232
00:11:58,252 --> 00:11:59,820
( Sniffing )

233
00:12:02,155 --> 00:12:04,557
- ( Roaring )
- ( Girl screaming )

234
00:12:04,591 --> 00:12:06,359
Jotaro: Hey.

235
00:12:07,394 --> 00:12:09,630
( Orangutan groans )

236
00:12:09,663 --> 00:12:11,331
Girl: Jojo!

237
00:12:12,566 --> 00:12:14,535
Jotaro: Take your lock,
you stinking ape.

238
00:12:17,171 --> 00:12:19,540
Seems that this ape...

239
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:21,442
Isn’t your
run-of-the-mill monkey.

240
00:12:21,475 --> 00:12:23,377
Could it be that he’s the one?

241
00:12:24,878 --> 00:12:26,780
Star platinum: Ora!

242
00:12:31,485 --> 00:12:33,253
( Orangutan laughs )

243
00:12:34,288 --> 00:12:35,356
Jotaro: Wait.

244
00:12:35,389 --> 00:12:37,258
Who the hell
ripped out that fan?

245
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:38,259
Had to be him.

246
00:12:38,292 --> 00:12:39,860
So this ape’s a stand user,

247
00:12:39,893 --> 00:12:41,528
but where’s the stand?

248
00:12:41,562 --> 00:12:44,298
I should be able to see
the damn thing, but I can’t.

249
00:12:44,331 --> 00:12:45,299
Doesn’t make any sense.

250
00:12:45,332 --> 00:12:47,134
What the--

251
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:49,403
the steel propeller
bent on its own,

252
00:12:49,436 --> 00:12:50,637
like it’s alive.

253
00:12:50,671 --> 00:12:52,573
- ( Orangutan roars )
- Girl: Jojo.

254
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:55,109
Jotaro: Hey,
what’s going on here?

255
00:12:55,142 --> 00:12:56,710
( Orangutan growls )

256
00:12:56,743 --> 00:12:58,245
( Roars )

257
00:12:58,278 --> 00:12:59,780
Jotaro: Son of a bitch.

258
00:12:59,813 --> 00:13:01,882
There’s no stand in sight,
and somehow the window broke?

259
00:13:01,915 --> 00:13:04,317
Star platinum!

260
00:13:06,486 --> 00:13:08,455
( Star platinum yells )

261
00:13:12,593 --> 00:13:15,496
( Orangutan grunting )

262
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:20,267
Jotaro: What’s with this thing?

263
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:23,436
The ape just sank into the wall
and disappeared.

264
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:25,672
Hey, you saw that, right?

265
00:13:25,706 --> 00:13:29,276
Stay close to me.
Something bad is going down.

266
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:32,479
The ape vanished into the wall,

267
00:13:32,513 --> 00:13:35,716
but that orangutan
has to be the stand user.

268
00:13:35,749 --> 00:13:37,451
When I touched it earlier,

269
00:13:37,484 --> 00:13:39,653
I felt a stand’s energy
coming from it.

270
00:13:39,686 --> 00:13:42,923
I have no doubt that he’s
the one we’re looking for.

271
00:13:42,956 --> 00:13:44,458
Doesn’t make any sense.

272
00:13:44,491 --> 00:13:47,227
Why can’t I see the stand,
like I always do?

273
00:13:47,261 --> 00:13:48,295
( Gasps )

274
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:49,796
Wait.

275
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:53,300
What if i’m seeing it already?

276
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,367
- ( Rumbling )
- ( Both gasp )

277
00:13:54,401 --> 00:13:55,502
Girl: What’s happening?

278
00:13:55,536 --> 00:13:56,804
( Men gasping )

279
00:13:56,837 --> 00:13:58,939
Avdol: Whoa. What’s going on?

280
00:13:58,972 --> 00:14:00,740
Joseph: This isn’t good.

281
00:14:00,774 --> 00:14:02,809
Polnareff: It’s swallowing us.

282
00:14:02,843 --> 00:14:04,645
Joseph: Is the freighter
trying to--

283
00:14:04,678 --> 00:14:07,347
is it possible
the ship itself is--

284
00:14:07,381 --> 00:14:10,951
jotaro: So the stand
is actually the freighter.

285
00:14:12,486 --> 00:14:14,788
( Orangutan laughs )

286
00:14:15,822 --> 00:14:18,591
Jotaro: Damn. You son of a...

287
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:19,759
Joseph: All of it,

288
00:14:19,793 --> 00:14:22,262
this ship itself
and everything on it,

289
00:14:22,296 --> 00:14:23,664
is a gigantic stand!

290
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:24,898
Polnareff: The entire ship?

291
00:14:24,932 --> 00:14:26,901
So there are stands
that non-stand users,

292
00:14:26,934 --> 00:14:29,603
like that girl
and the crew members, can see?

293
00:14:29,636 --> 00:14:31,371
Avdol: The only possible
explanation for that

294
00:14:31,405 --> 00:14:32,773
is that its immense energy

295
00:14:32,806 --> 00:14:35,242
is making it possible
to be seen with the naked eye.

296
00:14:35,275 --> 00:14:38,678
But all this must demand
a tremendous amount of energy

297
00:14:38,712 --> 00:14:41,782
to operate a stand
as huge as this.

298
00:14:41,815 --> 00:14:44,251
Kakyoin,
send hierophant green to jotaro.

299
00:14:44,284 --> 00:14:46,653
He can help get us out of this.

300
00:14:46,687 --> 00:14:48,355
Kakyoin: I...Can’t do that.

301
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:50,924
It’s got a firm hold
on my stand, and i’m stuck.

302
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:53,461
Polnareff: This is
what it means to face death.

303
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:55,962
We fell for this trap, and
now we’re hopelessly ensnared

304
00:14:55,996 --> 00:14:57,564
with no way to escape.

305
00:14:57,598 --> 00:14:58,899
( Kakyoin gasps )

306
00:14:58,932 --> 00:15:01,568
The pressure keeps increasing.

307
00:15:01,602 --> 00:15:04,872
At this rate, our bodies
are going to be pulverized.

308
00:15:04,905 --> 00:15:06,540
We...will be...

309
00:15:06,573 --> 00:15:08,375
Joseph: Damn. We were careless.

310
00:15:08,408 --> 00:15:10,543
We’ve got to--( Groans )

311
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:12,579
( Orangutan grunting )

312
00:15:18,685 --> 00:15:21,288
Narrator: The word that
the orangutan was pointing to

313
00:15:21,321 --> 00:15:22,823
was "strength."

314
00:15:22,856 --> 00:15:26,493
It means force, energy,
power, or aid,

315
00:15:26,527 --> 00:15:30,264
and it is the eighth card
of the tarot deck.

316
00:15:30,297 --> 00:15:32,299
It suggests challenge,

317
00:15:32,332 --> 00:15:35,535
a strong will,
and hidden powers.

318
00:15:39,339 --> 00:15:41,408
( Orangutan grunting )

319
00:15:44,044 --> 00:15:45,546
( Star platinum grunts )

320
00:15:45,579 --> 00:15:47,781
( Orangutan gasps )

321
00:15:49,349 --> 00:15:50,750
( Chuckling )

322
00:15:50,784 --> 00:15:54,454
Jotaro: Damn ape.
Thinks he’s won already, huh?

323
00:15:54,488 --> 00:15:58,525
Narrator: "This entire ship
is my stand, and you’ve lost.

324
00:15:58,559 --> 00:16:00,861
"You’re totally outmatched
and helpless,

325
00:16:00,894 --> 00:16:03,029
and there’s
nothing you can do."

326
00:16:03,063 --> 00:16:05,265
( Orangutan hooting )

327
00:16:05,299 --> 00:16:07,701
Narrator: Jotaro needed
no explanation.

328
00:16:07,734 --> 00:16:10,637
He knew exactly
what the ape was saying.

329
00:16:10,671 --> 00:16:12,640
( Orangutan grunts )

330
00:16:12,673 --> 00:16:14,642
( Girl whimpers )

331
00:16:14,675 --> 00:16:17,645
♪

332
00:16:17,678 --> 00:16:19,713
- ( Orangutan grunts )
- ( Girl yelps )

333
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:25,953
( Orangutan growls )

334
00:16:33,961 --> 00:16:35,930
( Growls )

335
00:16:37,965 --> 00:16:39,366
Jotaro: Over here, monkey.

336
00:16:39,399 --> 00:16:41,534
That button’s
not part of your stand.

337
00:16:41,568 --> 00:16:43,603
( Orangutan growls )

338
00:16:43,637 --> 00:16:45,606
( Jotaro scoffs ) Are you angry?

339
00:16:45,639 --> 00:16:47,441
I guess it wounded your pride,

340
00:16:47,474 --> 00:16:49,409
since you thought
you’d already beaten us.

341
00:16:49,443 --> 00:16:52,646
No, it’s not hurt at all, is it?

342
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:55,515
Because apes like you
don’t have any pride.

343
00:16:55,549 --> 00:16:57,751
( Orangutan roars )

344
00:16:57,784 --> 00:17:01,054
Jotaro: That’s exactly what
makes you an ape and not a man.

345
00:17:01,088 --> 00:17:02,856
Star platinum:
What’s going to hurt now...

346
00:17:02,890 --> 00:17:04,125
Is your head!

347
00:17:05,792 --> 00:17:07,927
( Orangutan screaming )

348
00:17:19,006 --> 00:17:20,574
Jotaro: Good grief.

349
00:17:20,607 --> 00:17:22,776
( Orangutan yelps )

350
00:17:22,809 --> 00:17:24,811
( Grunting )

351
00:17:27,648 --> 00:17:29,416
Jotaro: I’ve heard that,
when frightened,

352
00:17:29,449 --> 00:17:30,717
animals show their stomachs

353
00:17:30,751 --> 00:17:32,920
to signal their submission
to the enemy.

354
00:17:32,953 --> 00:17:35,122
So you’re asking me
to forgive you?

355
00:17:35,155 --> 00:17:37,524
( Orangutan grunting )

356
00:17:37,558 --> 00:17:39,593
Jotaro: I’m afraid your actions

357
00:17:39,626 --> 00:17:42,829
have already gone
beyond the rules of the jungle,

358
00:17:42,863 --> 00:17:45,733
so I don’t think so.

359
00:17:45,766 --> 00:17:48,736
( Star platinum yelling )

360
00:17:48,769 --> 00:17:50,771
Ora!

361
00:17:54,708 --> 00:17:56,410
( Girl yelps )

362
00:17:56,443 --> 00:17:57,844
What the--

363
00:17:57,878 --> 00:17:59,847
the pipes and walls
are distorting.

364
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,782
The whole ship is twisting up.

365
00:18:01,815 --> 00:18:04,017
Jotaro: Hey,
be surprised about it later.

366
00:18:04,051 --> 00:18:06,820
- This ship is about to sink.
- ( Girl gasps )

367
00:18:06,854 --> 00:18:10,024
Jotaro: It’s time to leave.
Get back to the lifeboats.

368
00:18:11,124 --> 00:18:13,126
♪

369
00:18:15,829 --> 00:18:17,964
Girl: Wow, I can’t believe it.

370
00:18:17,998 --> 00:18:19,900
The ship’s shape is changing.

371
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:22,636
It’s turning into
a shabby little boat.

372
00:18:22,669 --> 00:18:25,705
Avdol: If I hadn’t seen it
myself, I wouldn’t believe it.

373
00:18:25,739 --> 00:18:28,542
That ape was traveling the sea
on his own stand.

374
00:18:28,575 --> 00:18:30,544
What terrifying power.

375
00:18:30,577 --> 00:18:33,547
That was the first time
i’ve encountered such energy.

376
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:34,848
Joseph: Hate to say it,

377
00:18:34,882 --> 00:18:37,084
but we were completely
overwhelmed this round.

378
00:18:37,117 --> 00:18:41,054
If jotaro hadn’t figured it out,
we would have been done for.

379
00:18:41,088 --> 00:18:43,624
Are we going to encounter
even more stands

380
00:18:43,657 --> 00:18:45,826
with crazy, unknown powers
from now on?

381
00:18:45,859 --> 00:18:48,829
We’ll have to be ready
for anything.

382
00:18:48,862 --> 00:18:50,831
Polnareff: Hey,
you want some gum?

383
00:18:50,864 --> 00:18:54,000
Avdol: So we’re going
to be drifting again.

384
00:18:54,034 --> 00:18:56,069
Jotaro: Good grief.
My cigarettes are soaked.

385
00:18:56,103 --> 00:18:57,771
Polnareff:
There’ll be plenty of sun

386
00:18:57,804 --> 00:18:59,706
and time for them
to get dry, jojo.

387
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:02,176
Joseph: We’ll have to pray
that we get rescued

388
00:19:02,209 --> 00:19:05,112
and reach Singapore
safely and soon.

389
00:19:05,145 --> 00:19:08,181
Kakyoin: It’s been four days
since we left Japan.

390
00:19:08,215 --> 00:19:09,950
Narrator: There are 46 days

391
00:19:09,983 --> 00:19:12,886
until time runs out
for the joestars.

392
00:19:21,628 --> 00:19:25,966
Enyaba: My lord, it would appear
that strength has been defeated.

393
00:19:25,999 --> 00:19:27,634
But have no fear.

394
00:19:27,668 --> 00:19:30,871
The remaining six stand users
are all very powerful

395
00:19:30,904 --> 00:19:33,006
and each deadlier than the last,

396
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,075
and one of them is my son.

397
00:19:35,108 --> 00:19:37,744
His right arm
shall crush our enemies.

398
00:19:37,778 --> 00:19:40,014
The joestars
will not pose a threat

399
00:19:40,047 --> 00:19:42,216
when he’s finished with them.
( Laughs )

400
00:19:42,249 --> 00:19:43,784
( Dio chuckles )

401
00:19:43,817 --> 00:19:46,119
You are a strange old woman.

402
00:19:46,153 --> 00:19:48,622
What is it
that you desire the most?

403
00:19:48,655 --> 00:19:50,891
Enyaba: Oh,
but i’ve told you many times.

404
00:19:50,924 --> 00:19:53,927
My only wish is to stay
by your side, my lord.

405
00:19:53,961 --> 00:19:57,231
Your guardian spirit
has unbelievable power.

406
00:19:57,264 --> 00:20:00,234
Your ability to escape trouble
and your strange life

407
00:20:00,267 --> 00:20:02,736
are the result of that.

408
00:20:02,769 --> 00:20:06,940
I would like to see
your life unfold.

409
00:20:06,974 --> 00:20:09,243
It’s the only thing I want.

410
00:20:09,276 --> 00:20:11,678
♪

411
00:20:11,712 --> 00:20:13,214
Narrator: Once upon a time,

412
00:20:13,247 --> 00:20:15,916
there was a prince
from the land of sumatra

413
00:20:15,949 --> 00:20:18,285
who traveled the seas
seeking new lands.

414
00:20:18,318 --> 00:20:20,587
Eventually he happened
upon an island

415
00:20:20,621 --> 00:20:22,790
inhabited by lions
called singas,

416
00:20:22,823 --> 00:20:25,025
an island he named singapura.

417
00:20:26,059 --> 00:20:27,994
Today, its straits bustle

418
00:20:28,028 --> 00:20:30,030
with ships and tankers
from around the world.

419
00:20:30,063 --> 00:20:33,233
This nation that shares both
western and eastern heritage,

420
00:20:33,267 --> 00:20:36,070
thanks to free trade,
is tropical Singapore.

421
00:20:36,103 --> 00:20:38,906
Polnareff: Good grief.
We finally made it to dry land.

422
00:20:38,939 --> 00:20:41,275
Joseph: We’ll clean up
and get some rest at a hotel.

423
00:20:41,308 --> 00:20:43,877
Once we’ve recharged, we’ll
figure out our route to Egypt.

424
00:20:43,911 --> 00:20:46,914
All right,
let’s stay at that one.

425
